   1139           *   can't be used.
   1140           * @note
   1141           *   This function is incompatible with the Power Manager module. When the
   1142           *   Power Manager module is present, it must be the one deciding at which
   1143           *   EM level the device sleeps to ensure the application properly works. Using
   1144           *   both at the same time could lead to undefined behavior in the application.
   1145           * @par
   1146           *   If HFXO/LFXO/LFRCO are re-enabled by this function, and NOT used to clock
   1147           *   the core, this function will not wait for those oscillators to stabilize.
   1148           *   This must be considered by the application if trying to use features
   1149           *   relying on those oscillators upon return.
   1150           * @par
   1151           *   If a debugger is attached, the AUXHFRCO will not be disabled if enabled
   1152           *   upon entering EM3. It will, therefore, remain enabled when returning to EM0
   1153           *   regardless of the @p restore parameter.
   1154           * @par
   1155           *   If voltage scaling is supported, the restore parameter is true and the EM0
   1156           *   voltage scaling level is set higher than the EM3 level, then the EM0 level is
   1157           *   also restored.
   1158           * @par
